To save a `%` operation for every byte (which is essentially a division!) and add a sanity check for empty key, I suggest:
```c++
    void Xor(const std::string& key)
    {
        assert(key.size() > 0);
        for (size_type i = 0, j = 0; i != size(); i++) {
            vch[i] ^= key[j++];
            if (j == key.size())
                j = 0;
        }
    }
```

